parts:
I'm getting a TypeError in auth.ts when I run npm run build. The error says 'Cannot read properties of undefined (reading user)'. Here's my code:

function validate(req) {
  return req.user.id;
}

What am I doing wrong?

The TypeError happens because req.user is undefined when the request hasn't been authenticated yet. You need to guard the access or ensure the middleware runs first. Here's a safer version:

```typescript
function validate(req: Request): string | null {
  if (!req.user) return null;
  return req.user.id;
}
```

This fixes the immediate crash. The deeper issue is that your auth middleware likely isn't attached to this route.

You need to register the auth middleware before your route handlers. In your Express setup:

```typescript
import { authMiddleware } from './middleware/auth';

app.use(authMiddleware);
app.use('/api', apiRoutes);
```

Order matters — authMiddleware must come before the routes that need it.

Here's a minimal JWT middleware:

```typescript
import jwt from 'jsonwebtoken';
import type { Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';

export function authMiddleware(req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) {
  const header = req.header('Authorization');
  if (!header?.startsWith('Bearer ')) return res.status(401).json({ error: 'no token' });
  const token = header.slice(7);
  try {
    const payload = jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_SECRET!);
    (req as any).user = payload;
    next();
  } catch {
    res.status(401).json({ error: 'invalid token' });
  }
}
```

Make sure JWT_SECRET is set in your env.
